		</font>
		<hr size="1">Thanks for your replys.  I was just curious because of the problems i have on the bristlebane server.  Everyone thinks im nuts.  You know the conversation....<BR>Lithpy shouts "Selling POTIONS of SOW...Gimme a tell<P>customer "potions?  really, its not a spell?"<P>Lithpy "nope, its a potion you can carry with you and use when you need it"<P>customer "cool, how much?"<P>Lithpy "asking 20pp per"<P>customer "20pp for a freakin SOW, are you outta your mind.  Forget it"<P>then i once tried this<P>Lithpy "so what you willing to pay?"<P>customer " no more than 4pp, people cast them all the time"<P>So there you have it.  And its true, anyone in just about any zone can shout and offer 1pp and get a sow anywhere, anytime.  So why doesnt verant make it more money efficient for us to make this spell?  Sure we all get into this knowing that Alchemy is an expensive skill, but how are we supposed to afford it if noone will buy our potions, we spend all our cash working the skill, and a SoW potion sells back to a vendor for only 9gp with 112 cha.  Makes no sense.  I guess if i was lvl 50 and able to make 500pp in a few hours of play it wouldnt be that big of a deal.  But im not, so it is.  With an alchemy skill of only 27 now, i still fail at making the SoWs about 40% of the time.  And at about 11pp an attempt.....whats a broke shaman to do?<P>Lithpy, Barbarian Shaman of the 30th season<BR>Bristlebane server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
