		<a href="mailto:ccraig@smartt.com" target="_new">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/email.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Email ccraig" width="24" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=115&FN=Alchemy&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=393670&TN=%24%24+for+SOW+potions&CAT=Trade+Skills&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=393674&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I don't think the SoW potions were intended to compete with the spell.  They're a luxury item that only high levels can afford.  Some use them for emergency use, when no druids or shammys are around, and others (like necros) buy in semi-bulk to kite with.  Hence they'll sell quicker in higher level zones...SolB; Oasis and Feerot (Spec hunters); Rathe Mtns; or anywhere high levels are likely to be (druid rings, cities etc.).<P>I've personally sold over 50 SoW potions so far.  They don't sell quickly, they're a bit of a pain in the ass...that's one of the reasons why I won't charge less than 20pp.<P>If someone tells you you're nuts for charging 20pp, that SoW sells for 1pp, tell them they sell to high levels characters.  Chances are, if someone is balking at paying 20pp, they aren't a potential client anyways.<P>I didn't fail 40% of the time at 27 skill, maybe 30%.  Perhaps you need more Wis jewelry?  I personally carry around 8 items I use EXCLUSIVELY for making potions (increasing Int and Wis). <P>Here's another tidbit, and maybe it's just superstition (others have mentioned it as well), but I think the order in which you put the herbs in the bag matters.  I once failed FIVE TIMES in a row on SoW when it was trivial!  So I went back to: Birthwort in top left slot, Fennugreek to the right of it, and Wolfblood below the Birthwort.   Who knows, maybe it makes a difference.<P>Because of the low rate of sale, don't expect the skill to increase quickly, you'll have to be patient, and take the sales when they come.  Auction whenever you zone.  Unless you have 11k pp to blow selling them back to vendors  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"><P>My 2cp, hope it's useful.<P>Rimamok Ralgazek<BR>Oggur Shamun uf 34 bonks<BR>Brell<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
