		<hr size="1">A follow-up to my original post:<P>After hearing about SOW potions and then seeing this thread I just had to have a few.  I'm a Barbarian Warrior who spends most of his time soloing.<P>This information is just to help those of you that make sow potions...and maybe those of you considering making them and selling them.<P>This spell is a necessity! You should have no trouble selling these potions at all! Anyone who doesn't have the ability to SOW themselves NEEDS at least 1 of these potions on them at all times!<P>Yesterday I bought 3 potions for 45pp at the EC tunnel. The seller asked for 15pp...I tried to haggle down to 12pp and failed. Realizing how much I needed these potions I dug down deep and handed over the 45pp.<P>Here is a suggestion for you alchemists:<P>Learn how to sell this vital potion! Do not just...<P>/auc WTS SOW potions<P>This doesn't do you justice.<P>Try this...<P>/shout Selling SOW potions at 20pp each...these are a MUST and will save your life!<P>Just add some spice to your message. There are so many sales happening at the same time that your awesome potion goes by without much notice.<P>I don't suggest shouting an auction very often..but when there is intense competiton it may be your only way of being heard.<P>When you get tells from potential buyers I would do some serious selling. Don't just quote the price! You have a very valuable potion that THEY NEED!<P>Try some of these...<P>/tell Mr. Customer This potion should be kept at the ready so that when you need to run and escape you can quickly drink it! It will save your life, save your time, and save your level!<P>Now you are selling! I happened to tell myself this...the seller didn't. I know how much I need SOW to escape a bad situation so I'm really excited about having these in my inventory now. I plan on buying an entire backpack full and keeping it in the bank so I never run out.<P>Broadblade out.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
